@startuml
title Multi-Agent Interaction Sequence - Stock Query

actor User
participant "Chat UI" as UI
participant "Orchestrator\nAgent" as ORC
participant "Risk &\nCompliance" as RC
participant "Market Data\nAgent" as MD
participant "News\nAgent" as NA
participant "Sentiment\nAgent" as SA
participant "Fundamental\nAgent" as FA
participant "Advisory\nAgent" as ADV

User -> UI: "What do you think about AAPL?"
UI -> ORC: Forward user message

== Intent Recognition ==
ORC -> ORC: Parse intent: stock_query\nExtract ticker: AAPL
ORC -> RC: Pre-filter input for injection
RC --> ORC: Input clean

== Parallel Data Collection ==
ORC -> MD: Request AAPL market data
ORC -> NA: Request AAPL news
activate MD
activate NA

MD -> MD: Fetch price, volume, market cap
MD -> MD: Calculate SMA, RSI, MACD
MD --> ORC: Market data + technical indicators
deactivate MD

NA -> NA: Query 2+ news sources
NA -> NA: Deduplicate & score relevance
NA --> ORC: Top-N news articles
deactivate NA

== Sequential Analysis ==
ORC -> SA: Analyze news sentiment
activate SA
SA -> SA: Score each article (-1 to +1)
SA -> SA: Generate reasoning chain
SA --> ORC: Sentiment scores + reasoning
deactivate SA

par Parallel Analysis
  ORC -> FA: Analyze fundamentals
  activate FA
  FA -> FA: Calculate P/E, P/B, ROE
  FA -> FA: Peer comparison + red flags
  FA --> ORC: Fundamental report
  deactivate FA
else
  ORC -> RC: Assess risk
  activate RC
  RC -> RC: Calculate beta, volatility
  RC -> RC: Score risk 1-10
  RC --> ORC: Risk assessment
  deactivate RC
end

== Recommendation Synthesis ==
ORC -> ADV: All analysis results
activate ADV
ADV -> ADV: Weigh dimensions\n(Fundamental 35%, Sentiment 25%\nRisk 25%, Technical 15%)
ADV -> ADV: Generate Buy/Hold/Sell
ADV -> ADV: Assemble reasoning chain
ADV --> ORC: Recommendation + reasoning
deactivate ADV

== Compliance & Response ==
ORC -> RC: Post-filter output
RC -> RC: Inject disclaimer
RC --> ORC: Compliant response

ORC --> UI: Formatted response\nwith reasoning trace
UI --> User: Display recommendation\n+ expandable reasoning

@enduml
